name: Zipline
description: Zipline Brewing Co. crafts artisan ales and lagers with high quality precision in Lincoln, Nebraska. Born from the founders’ innate sense of adventure and their desire to connect with the thrill-seeking spirit in all craft beer fans.

name: Empyrean
description: Empyrean Brewing Co. began in 1991 with a dream that they could hand-craft full-flavored beer. The dream became Nebraska’s first microbrewery, Empyrean Brewing Co.

name: Lazy Horse
description: Nested in the Nebraska Heartland, come enjoy its rural beauty and unique selection of beers.

name: Kinkaider
description: We are a Farm Craft Brewery with locations is Lincoln, Grand Island, and Broken Bow. Stop by our 3 locations and enjoy our award-winning beers!

name: Infusion
description: Infusion Brewery now occupies the former home of Olson’s Meat Market in Downtown Benson. When the building became available, Bill Baburek, owner of Omaha’s Crescent Moon, decided to turn his dream of opening a craft brewery into reality.

name: Kros Strain
description: Two dudes with a passion for brewing great beers, founders Bobby Kros and Scott Strain, started Kros Strain Brewing. Known to innovate, the pair will tinker with recipes, until it’s not just “good enough” – but until it’s freaking great.
locationDescription: On Portal Road in La Vista, NE

name: Nebraska Brewing
description: With a foundation in homebrewing in 1992, Paul Kavulak set about to experiment within a hobby that would prove to change the landscape of Nebraska Craft Beer.
locationDescription: On 108th Street in La Vista, NE

name: Lucky Bucket
description: Hoppy libations, barrel aged ales, bold stouts, tart sour beers – you name it, ucky Bucket brews it!
locationDescription: On Centennial Road in La Vista, NE

name: Brickway
description: Since 2013, Brickway Brewery & Distillery has been brewing staple beers and whisky in the Historic Old Market District.

name: Backswing
description: For the true beer drinker and beer novice alike, Backswing Brewing offers a break from the pretentiousness of craft beer by meticulously crafting easy-drinking, true-to-style beer.

name: Code
description: Located in the Telegraph District in Lincoln, Nebraska, Code Beer is laid-back place to try great new brews.
breweryAddress: 200 S Antelope Valley Pkwy, Lincoln, NE

name: Cosmic
description: Cosmic Eye is a family owned brewery and tap room located at 6800 P ST Lincoln, NE.

name: White Elm
description: White Elm Brewing Company strives to bring modern takes on rustic ales to southeast Nebraska.

name: Bottle Rocket
description: Bottle Rocket has a  mission is to brew superior craft beer for patrons in Seward and throughout the Midwest.

name: Thunderhead
description: Founded in 1999, Thunderhead Brewing is a small brewmaster owned brewery dedicated to producing high quality ales and lagers.
locationDescription: On F Ave in Axtell, NE.

name: Pint Nine
description: Located in La Vista, Pint Nine is commited to tradition and innovation.
locationDescription: On Portal Road in La Vista, NE

name: 1st Street
description: First Street Brewing Co. is located in the heart of Downtown Hastings, Nebraska. We believe in making great beer that exemplifies truly regional flavors.
breweryAddress: 119 N. Saint Joseph Ave., Hastings, NE

name: Prairie Pride
description: We believe, with great pride, that craft beer is an attitude and that flavor favors the bold. That bold attitude is what led us to imagine the Hopffalo as the perfect symbol for our mutual pride of place and love of craft beer.
breweryAddress: 115 E South Front St, Suite 1 Grand Island, NE

name: Flyover
description: The first brewery in the Nebraska Panhandle, Flyover Brewing Company takes pride in brewing. Brewed by an award winning professional brewer with years of experience in the craft, the brewery produces both true to style lagers and ales along with innovative locally themed brews.

name: Brewery 719
description: At Brewery 719 we understand and appreciate a hard days work, especially when it comes to a craft brew from the heartland. Our work is a labor of love and we reap the fruits of our labor every day.
